What is IAM?

IAM (Identity and Access Management) controls who can access AWS and what they can do.

Why is IAM needed?
1) Prevent unauthorized access
2) Give limited permissions (least privilege)
3) Manage users securely

IAM Main Concepts 
👤 User

A person (you, admin, developer)

👥 Group

Collection of users with the same permissions

📜 Policy

Permission rules written in JSON
(Example: allow EC2, deny S3)

🎭 Role

Temporary permission given to services
(EC2 accessing S3)
